"{\n  \"text\": \"So I'm gonna start selling my garden vegetables at the farmers market, and I think this is an excellent thing for others to do. I hope this works out. I hope that I can create enough of a market for myself to justify this. I help through the videos that other people could see the same markets, other people can start looking for the same foods at their farmers' markets, and doing this type of thing because I see this as a real opportunity to change the way we live our lives. We become food and water sufficient is the first step towards independence of everything. Once we have as a community, not just in isolation, but once all these houses and all these cities have backyards full of growing vegetables and growing, you know, water, they really don't have that much they can do to us. Everything else after that is kind of a luxury. If we can take care of our own food and water, then the rest of it is negotiable. Then we truly have our power and our freedom, and that's where we can do things. I remember listening to uh Big Mike, the rapper of Run the Jewels talking about this somewhere where and he's such a great guy. Like I love his message. But he was talking to all these people who were preaching revolution and we need to do this, we need to do that. And he's like, How many of y'all get a single calorie not from the man? How many of y'all are in any way independent from the structure of the way we live that's provided by the man that you're trying to overthrow or do something about? He's like, You're completely under his thumb. You have no place to criticize anything because you can't do without it. I was like, oof, dang, big Mike. And so, you know, I'm trying to do this to kind of inspire other people to do it. Because honestly, I think that like if you're looking at a household with two earners, one of those earners should stay at home and provide the calories for the family and provide the water and provide the, you know, get the the necessities, 